</CENTER><BR><TABLE WIDTH=95%><TR><TD><B><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Council of Guilds</FONT></A></B><BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsguildwars><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Guildwars</FONT></A></B><BR><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Issues about Guildwars</FONT></B></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsguildwars.showAddTopicScreenFromWeb><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/newTopic.gif border=0></A>&nbsp; <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsguildwars.showAddPollScreenFromWeb><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/newPoll.gif border=0></A>&nbsp; <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsguildwars.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsguildwars.showMessage?topicID=5.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1><< Prev Topic</FONT></A> &nbsp;<A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsguildwars.showMessage?topicID=9.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Next Topic >></FONT></A> </TD></TR></TABLE><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="95%"><tr><td bgcolor=#000000><table border=0 width=100% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><TR><TD valign=top BGCOLOR=#8E9173><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top BGCOLOR=#8E9173><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#FFFFCC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Administrator</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#8E9173>5/25/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#8E9173>11:24:19 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Issues about Guildwars</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">This was posted by Abashi in the last couple of days, and it directly relates to guildwars and PvP situations on Karana (and other normal servers):<br>
<br>
                      [Quote from original post: #1 - Exp loss from DoT spells * For months, players killed<br>
                      by a DoT spell<br>
                      would lose experience. Very unfair to those without DoT spells of course. Such an<br>
                      obvious problem<br>
                      surely had to have been tested/known before opening PvP servers.] <br>
<br>
                      This issue was addressed on the PvP servers shortly after TZ and VZ launched. It still<br>
                      exists<br>
                      on the normal servers for PvP people and people who engage in duels. Due to the way<br>
                      DOTs<br>
                      work, changing this aspect beyond its current state is not feasible. <br>
<br>
                      [Quote from original post: #2 - DoT casters can't loot victims * Even to this day,<br>
                      when soemone dies<br>
                      due to DoT, the caster cannot loot that victim. Very unfair to those with DoT as their<br>
                      main form of<br>
                      damage.] <br>
<br>
                      This issue is the same problem that causes/caused XP loss due to DOTs. As with the<br>
                      issue<br>
                      above, changing it beyond its current state is not feasible. <br>
<br>
                      [Quote from original post: #3 - Exp loss from pet death * For months, people who<br>
                      were killed by<br>
                      someone's pet would lose exp. Very unfair to those without pets, and to those<br>
                      casters with pets who<br>
                      hated to make that happen but were left with little choice. Surely Verant knew about<br>
                      that problem.] <br>
<br>
                      I don't know off the top of my head if this still happens in PvP situations (/duel,<br>
                      guildwar,<br>
                      etc.) on non-PvP servers, but it has been correct on the PvP servers. The exception<br>
                      to this is<br>
                      cases where owner of the pet is LD or under the effect of Fear (cast by an NPC since<br>
                      PCs can<br>
                      fear each other any longer). As with the issues above, addressing these exceptions is<br>
                      not<br>
                      feasible, and we'll consider any cases of intentional abuse a customer-service issue. <br>
<br>
                      [Quote from original post: #5 - Charm/Fear taken out of game * Due to problems that<br>
                      would occur to<br>
                      people who got charmed/feared (such as being treated as an npc and bearing full bore<br>
                      spell damage<br>
                      instead of the nerfed rate, etc etc.), verant simply too charm and fear out of the<br>
                      game. For<br>
                      enchanters, clerics, necros, sk's and others, that was a major blow to their offense.<br>
                      Instead of fixing<br>
                      the game code problems, Verant simply trashed a major component to entire classes.]<br>
<br>
<br>
                      The nature of these spells made them abusable beyond all repair. People would fear<br>
                      people<br>
                      in dungeons, where they wouldn't break out until in deep an alone causing XP loss.<br>
                      People<br>
                      would charm people and have them attack nasty critters and die, causing XP loss.<br>
                      People<br>
                      would charm people and sit them down next to NPCs that are aggro to the native race<br>
                      of the<br>
                      target, but not to the charmer. When charm broke, the NPC would attack the person<br>
                      who was<br>
                      charmed causing XP loss. People would also keep other people charmed for extended<br>
                      periods<br>
                      of time thus denying their ability to play the game. The only solution that would have<br>
                      allowed<br>
                      these spells to remain in-game would be to eliminate XP loss entirely, which would too<br>
                      drastically change the PvE apsects of the game. <br>
<br>
                      &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;<br>
<br>
                      So the DOT problem is not going away, and neither is the pet damage problem. I'm<br>
                      beginning to think that in order to not invalidate certain classes and their abilities, we<br>
                      are going to have to allow DOT's and pets and just take the risk that someone will<br>
                      lose experience in the storylines and the guildwars. <br>
<br>
                      I myself, am not really worried about my own exp. loss. I don't like losing exp. but I'm<br>
                      in this for fun, and these kinds of things are more fun to me than the regular<br>
                      &quot;hunt-kill-loot&quot; cycle of the EQ game. So if it takes losing some exp., no big deal for<br>
                      me, I accept that. <br>
<br>
                    But these are probably issues that the two guilds/two combatants are going to have to decide for themselves. One class I'm thinking is completely nerfed by no-DOT's and no Pets is necros, but I've never played one, so let me know.<br>
<br>
                      Haemish MacLennan<br>
Clan Chieftan<br>
The Silver Daggers</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#CBC6B1><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uazuriem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azuriem</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#8E9173>8/16/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#8E9173>3:10:32 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Issues about Guildwars</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Can we not have a cleric with full XP rez on standbye to help assist those who lose xp?<br>
