High Elf Cleric of Tunare<br>
Founder of the Illuminatus Guild.<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#CBC6B1><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>ezOP</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#8E9173>8/16/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#8E9173>11:59:14 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Issues about Guildwars</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Unfortunately, my experience has been that unless it is a Verant sponsored event, GM's wouldn't help in this way at all, because it might show &quot;favoritism&quot; for one guild over another. The GM's have been unable and/or unwilling to help player-driven events in any way. <br>
<br>
However, I also had the idea about hiring a cleric to stand by with resses for the whole day of the guildwar. It would certainly make me happy if that could be done on a regular basis. <br>
<br>
But, even better, from what I have found in the latest guildwar event the Silver Daggers had recently (a fight involving close to 20 people between the Daggers and the Guardians of Innoruuk) was that these issues have been fixed. I have heard no report of any exp. loss from death due to another player from this event. And there were necros with DOT's, and both shaman and enchanter pets as well. If anyone lost exp. they haven't reported it to me, and we played with no restrictions on spells or pets. <br>
<br>
Hopefully, exp. loss in guildwars is a thing of the past.<br>
<br>
